               <p>ELLIS-
               <persName id="t18011202-68-person580">
                  THOMAS 
                  RODWELL
               <interp inst="t18011202-68-person580" type="surname" value="RODWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18011202-68-person580" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18011202-68-person580" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I live at <placeName id="t18011202-68-crimeloc363">No. 61, Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18011202-68-crimeloc363" type="placeName" value="No. 61, Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18011202-68-crimeloc363" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18011202-68-off361 t18011202-68-crimeloc363"></join>: On Wednesday, the 4th of November, I went from the front shop to the parlour, and had not been gone five minutes when the prisoner was brought back with the dowlas, which I saw at the door when I went to dinner; I know this to be the same by the mark on it. (The dowlas produced.)</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18011202-68-person581">
                  JOHN 
                  BOON
               <interp inst="t18011202-68-person581" type="surname" value="BOON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18011202-68-person581" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18011202-68-person581" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a weaver; I saw that lad run by with the goods, and thought he had stole it, so I ran after him; he sell down and I caught hold of him; he said, if you will let me go I will take it back to where I got it; I took him to the prosecutor's and left him and the dowlas in charge.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. There was a man with me of the name of Hodges; he bid me take it; but I don't know where he is.</p>
               <p>GUILTY, aged 12.</p>
               <p>
